@startuml
start
:The user starts SSH port forwarding to the remote GraphleManager;
:The user configures the server URL to the forwarded local port;
:The user opens the Graphle GUI;
if (Connection established?) then (Yes)
  :GraphleManager opens the configured home location;
  :The application shows neighbors from the remote filesystem;
  if (Open selected file?) then (Yes)
    :The GUI downloads a local copy or opens the file in place when configured as local;
  endif
else (No)
  :The system shows a connection error;
  :The user fixes or restarts the SSH tunnel;
endif
stop
@enduml
